<br>
And does it follow the classic 8 element system found in most of the FFs (Fire, Ice, Thunder, Earth, Wind, Water, Holy, Shadow)? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eaminwhitefalcon@graffeswizardcompilation>Eamin Whitefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>¡Viva la inquisición!</span><br>  Posts: 7453<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/03 2:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An EQ player's take on Final Fantasy XI (Info Bomb).</span><hr size=1> BTW, this writeup kicks much ass. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zerlatikflaimweaver>Zerlatik Flaimweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 239<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/03 2:54 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An EQ player's take on Final Fantasy XI (Info Bomb).</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>More details, please. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ok, Whiz, here's the skinny if you didn't see it in the other sections.  S-E's trying to capture the feeling of other final fantasy series games by trying to convince you that your character is a vital actor in the big play.  The game is crawling with cutscenes, thus when your party or your character accomplishes something, you get immediate visual feedback.  Instead of the text prompts we got in like the coldain shawl line, we get stuff happening on screen to let us know what's going down.  Usually the cutscenes will leak out more details about the backstory too.  In addition, they've keyed everything so that you need to advance the story to gain access to certain missions or quests, making the game a giant playable story with multiple characters.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Just one question: does the Summoner job get to summon Bahamut?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
To be honest, Eamin, I don't know.  I do know that you only start out with one summons, and then have to fight your way up to the others.  You gain summons by tracking them down and beating them in battle.  I know for sure that you can get Ifrit, Shiva, Titan, Leviathan, Garuda and Ramuh, just not sure on the others.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It sounds pretty cool, but... It also seems like something I would rather play single-player...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, Nadiar, if single player's your thing, I'd wait for FFXII, which is scheduled for release next year and will be the next in the single player line.  Playing this is kinda like playing any of the Tolkein online games, it allows you to interact with other fans of the series online and do the kind of stuff you've always wished you could do with other people watching.  Thankfully, it appears to be better than most of the LoTR or Wheel of Time MMORPGs.  It's like playing regular Final Fantasy, but only controlling one character at a time, with your friends on the others.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I also have a question. How is the sound and music?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, Goladus, I can sort of answer this, I'm not sure how important music is as far as introductions and such, but I do know who did the music and how well it seems to be done.  Nobuo Uematsu, who composed much of the series is playing a more limited role in this one, he's moved from composer to producer of much of the music.  S-E's got Naoshi Mizuta doing most of the music and almost all of the expansion tracks.  That said, S-E appears to be pretty confident on how it was done, because they've released soundtracks for both the main game and the expansion pack, and neither seems to be doing poorly.  Here's a link to a review of the music for you to look at: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.gamesarefun.com/music/reviews/f-ff-ffxiost.shtml" target="top">www.gamesarefun.com/music/reviews/f-ff-ffxiost.shtml</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Keep questions coming, I'll try to keep tracking down answers. BTW, any comments on my question from the last installment here? <p><center><b><u>The Man's Prayer</u></b><BR>
<center>I'm a man<BR>
<center>But I can change<BR>
<center>If I have to<BR>
