<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Are there religions?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->  <br>
<br>
Well, not really.  You're all basically warriors of light, the main difference is going to be your faction, which plays triple duty as nation, ideology and worldview.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And does it follow the classic 8 element system found in most of the FFs (Fire, Ice, Thunder, Earth, Wind, Water, Holy, Shadow)? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yup, those are the crystal types.  You use each of them to create items and infuse weapons with abilities.  4 common types, 4 rare, I forget exactly which is which though.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, you might get a kick out of this too.  You have weather effects, and they each play a role in the gameplay.  For instance, the summoner quest requires you be present in a specific area during a weather effect.  Also, if it rains, for instance, water elementals start spawning in the zone.  I would suspect spells and such work differently in different weathers, but don't quote me on that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eaminwhitefalcon@graffeswizardcompilation>Eamin Whitefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>¡Viva la inquisición!</span><br>  Posts: 7455<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/03 3:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An EQ player's take on Final Fantasy XI (Info Bomb).</span><hr size=1> !!!!!!!!!<br>
<br>
HOT DAMN! ÜBER! I guess that would be a reason to diversify your elemental attacks as a Black Mage, eh? You could use Thunder on water elementals during rainstorms, and Water on thunder elementals during lightning storms.<br>
<br>
This game is sounding cooler and cooler. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=milaru00>Milaru 00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1726<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/03 6:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An EQ player's take on Final Fantasy XI (Info Bomb).</span><hr size=1> oh fuck me, good bye sun, hello surgically implanted PS2 controls~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=healo>Healo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/03 7:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An EQ player's take on Final Fantasy XI (Info Bomb).</span><hr size=1> man i been waiting to play this game ever since it went live in Japan.  must have FF11...must have FF11...BBRRRAAAIIIINNNSSSSSSSSSSS!!!!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<br>Err, Forum Arch Mage?</span><br>  Posts: 4871<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/03 9:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An EQ player's take on Final Fantasy XI (Info Bomb).</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&lt;Edit&gt; What do you know, turns out the HTML filter just didn't like the way I was doing arrows. It's alwa